sentences: Keller's debut album, Sparks Are Gonna Fly, was released by Broken Bow Records in April 2000.
She was inducted into the Nebraska Music Hall of Fame in 2009.

The album received a mixed review from Joel Bernstein of Country Standard Time, who wrote that "it's too smooth and polished to grab the hard-core honkytonkers, but it's often too country for much of today's younger audience."
